directions: Break pretzels into bite size pieces.
Then place pretzels in a large mixing bowl minus any crumbs which will soak up the dressing. Mix ingredients in a separate bowl and pour over the pretzels.
Mix pretzels and ingredients well.
After mixing, put pretzels in a pan, approximately 11 x 9 1/2-inch.
Put in preheated oven at 350° for 5 minutes.
Then take out.
Pour back into mixing bowl and mix well again.
Then place pretzels back in oven 5 more minutes. Remove and drain on paper towel.

title: watergate salad
directions: Drain pineapple and reserve juice.
Place pudding mix in large bowl.
Add about 4 tablespoons of the pineapple juice to make a soft paste.
Mix well.
Add drained pineapple, whipped topping, marshmallows and chopped nuts.
Mix well until mixture is fluffy and increases in volume.
Refrigerate until chilled.

title: pam's meat loaf
directions: Soak bread crumbs in milk; add meat, eggs, onion and seasonings.
Mix well.
Form in individual loaves; place in greased muffin pans.
Cover with Piquant Sauce.
Bake in a moderate 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.
Or form one loaf in 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch pan.
Spread with sauce; bake 1 hour.

title: chili
directions: *Or whatever you want to use, as long as it is 18 ounces of "something."

title: 24-karat cake or cupcakes
directions: To make icing, beat butter or margarine with cream cheese in bowl of an electric mixer until very light and fluffy.

Beat in powdered sugar, followed by vanilla, pecans and optional coconut. To frost the cake, spread a generous amount of filling between and over the top of the layers, leaving the sides of the cake unfrosted.
Or use the icing to generously frost the top of the cupcakes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix soup, milk, sour cream and shredded cheese together and stir into the frozen potatoes.
Bake in glass dish or 1 1/2-quart greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, uncovered.

title: coney island sauce
directions: Mix all together and simmer 15 minutes.

title: apple crisps
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Place apples into buttered pan.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Sprinkle over apples.
Bake until brown.

title: sausage and potato stew
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan, heat potatoes, salt and enough water to cover to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes or until potatoes are fork-tender.
Drain.
While potatoes are boiling, in a 12-inch skillet, heat butter.
Cook onions until tender.
Add sausage, tomatoes with liquid, paprika, caraway seed and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Stir in potatoes and serve.

title: pistachio pudding dessert
directions: Mix all ingredients and press into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 325°.

title: sweet and easy corn pudding
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Conventional oven bake 45 minutes at 375°.
In microwave oven, microwave on High 4 minutes, stir; 4 minutes more, stir; 4 minutes more.
Should be like pudding.

title: barbecued shish kabobs
directions: Cut the first 5 ingredients into strips or chunks.
After cutting veggies and meat, saute chopped onion and garlic in oil. Stir in remaining ingredients; cook until slightly thickened. Thread meat and veggies on skewers.
Brush with sauce.
Place skewers on grill.
Cook for approximately 10 minutes, or until done.
Baste with remaining sauce while cooking.

title: fruitcake
directions: (You can substitute other candied fruit.)

title: hawaiian baked chicken
directions: Skin and wash chicken breasts.
Pat dry.
Place in a shallow pan.
Mix pineapple juice, soy sauce, oil and ginger.
Cover chicken with marinade and cover.
Refrigerate for 8 hours; turn pieces over once.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Pour off marinade, reserving liquid.
Bake chicken for 20 minutes; baste every 10 minutes.
Turn chicken pieces over and bake for another 30 minutes.
Continue to baste every 10 minutes, until chicken is done.
Serves 4.

title: nancy luthy's festive chowder
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Stir in celery and chopped onion; cook until tender.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper, if desired. Gradually add milk, stirring constantly.
Add potatoes.
Bring to boil; simmer 15 minutes, until potatoes are tender.
Add bacon and Crab Delights.
Heat 3 to 5 minutes more.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cafeteria cookies
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter, oatmeal and vanilla.
Stir.
Drop on wax paper. Refrigerate 1/2 hour.

title: garlic bubble bread
directions: Thaw and soften bread dough. Blend together melted butter, egg, garlic powder, parsley and salt. Cut off pieces of dough about size of small walnuts. Dip into butter mixture. Place pieces of dough into greased loaf pan until all dough is used. Cover. Let rise until double in size. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes. Brush with melted butter or margarine. Cool on wire rack. Makes 1 loaf.

title: old fashioned jam cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add jam.
Beat eggs and add milk. Sift flour in.
Add other ingredients.
Bake at 325°.

title: coconut island cookies
directions: In large mixer bowl combine chocolate, coffee, butter, brown sugar, egg, sour cream, flour, soda, salt and 1/3 cup coconut. Mix on lowest speed until a dough forms.
Drop by rounded teaspoon onto greased cookie sheets 12 to 15 minutes.
Frost warm. Sprinkle with remaining coconut.

title: gay's pineapple banana slush punch
directions: Dissolve sugar in water to make a light syrup.
Mix syrup with next three ingredients and pour into small containers to freeze solid.
Approximately 1 hour before serving, remove containers from freezer and place in punch bowl.
Pour ginger ale over frozen ingredients.
As mixture thaws, rake a fork over ice mixture to make slushy.

title: chop suey
directions: In a Dutch oven, bring water to a boil.
After rinsing off sprouts, simmer for ten minutes.
Bias cut celery and onions into semi-large pieces.
Add to sprouts and simmer another five minutes.
While you are cooking the vegetables, cut meat into whatever size pieces you desire.

title: scalloped tomatoes
directions: Stir all ingredients into well-beaten eggs.
Pour into greased oven dish.
Place dish in pan with some water.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until custard is set.
Serve hot.

title: pecan tarts
directions: Do not prebake pastry.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients. Mix well and put into baking dish. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cake
directions: Pour water over oatmeal; let stand 10 minutes.
Add sugar and margarine; stir well.
Add eggs.
Sift and add dry ingredients. Add 6 ounces chocolate chips.
Put in greased cake pan.
Sprinkle on top 3/4 cup nuts and 6 ounces chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Put stuffing mix in a greased, flat 3-quart casserole.
Top with cheese, then sausage.
Beat eggs, milk, soup and mustard together, then add mushrooms and pour over other ingredients in casserole.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: instant love
directions: Take friendship and love and mix them with tenderness.
Blend thoroughly with loyalty.
Add hope and faith.
Sprinkle with forgiveness.
Serve daily with abundant laughter.

title: hot chicken casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Place in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Best if mixed the day before.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chinese pepper steak
directions: Brown meat in a small amount of oil.
Add chopped onions, water and salt.
Cover and simmer until tender, about 20 minutes. Add green peppers and cook 5 minutes.
Blend cornstarch with a little water and add to meat mixture.
Cook, stirring, until thick.
Just before serving, add tomatoes and soy sauce; heat. Serve over rice.

title: fudge pie
directions: Combine all ingredients; pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Serve with a scoop of vanilla ice cream or whipped topping.

title: beef and squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion in salted water, about 5 minutes.
Drain well.
Cook green pepper and meat until meat is no longer pink. Stir in rice.
Blend eggs, soup, sour cream and seasonings; stirring into meat mixture.
Fold in squash mixture.
Turn into a greased 11 1/2 X 7 1/2 X 1 1/2 baking dish.
Top with cheese. Sprinkle with paprika, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Makes 8 servings.

title: sweet-sour meatballs
directions: Mix ground beef, cracker crumbs, minced onion, egg, milk and ginger.
Shape into meatballs; brown them on baking sheet in a 350° oven.
Mix cornstarch and sugar.
Stir in pineapple syrup, vinegar and soy sauce until smooth.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Put meatballs in casserole; add syrup mixture, pineapple and green pepper.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: chinese hamburg casserole
directions: Do not salt anything.
Brown hamburger in 2 to 3 tablespoons butter, add pepper.
Remove meat from frypan, put in vegetables and cook until tender.
Add 2 to 3 tablespoons of water to keep from burning.
Cook rice, when done add soy sauce and canned soups.
Add meat and rice mixture to vegetables.
Mix ingredients well and put into covered dish and bake 30 to 40 minutes.
A half cup water may be added, if needed.
Can be frozen before baking.

title: spanish rice
directions: Bring to a boil in 2-quart saucepan in 1 1/4 quarts of water. Add ingredients.
After 3 or 4 minutes, add rice; cut down heat and simmer for 10 minutes or until rice is cooked.
Use bigger pan if needed.

title: grammy's oatmeal crispies cookies
directions: Optional:
Add raisins or chocolate chips if you drop cookies.

title: friendship tea
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Seal in airtight container.
When ready to use, put 3 or 4 teaspoons in cup.
Fill with boiling water.
This mix makes a lovely gift.

title: wild rice rose(serve with lamb or chicken)
directions: Soak rice overnight; drain.
Wash and drain.
Mix with remaining ingredients.
Place in buttered 2-quart casserole dish. Cover and bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: beer-battered bass
directions: Combine pancake mix, flour, baking powder and salt in bowl. Add egg and beer; mix until smooth.
Dip fish in batter, coating well.
Deep fry in hot oil until golden brown; drain.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: apple jello salad
directions: In a saucepan, heat applesauce until it bubbles.
Stir in Jell-O and cook until dissolved.
Remove and cool, then stir in pop, orange juice and peel.
Chill until partially set, then stir in apples and nuts.
Chill until set firm.

title: spicy orange chicken
directions: Combine flour, salt, pepper and garlic powder in a bag.
Shake the chicken pieces individually until coated.
Brown in the butter in a skillet over medium-high heat, pour off fat.
In a bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
Add to skillet and simmer, covered, 25 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Serves 4.

title: butter cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix with a mixer until dough forms and color lightens.
Shape into small balls.
Bake at 325° until just done, not brown.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: monkey bread
directions: Grease tube pan.
Cut each biscuit into fourths.
Shake in a bag with sugar and cinnamon.
Put a layer of pecans (1 cup) and 1/2 biscuit mixture in pan and repeat this.
Pour mixture of brown sugar and margarine over all of this.
Bake at 350° for about 30 to 40 minutes.

title: quick fix oyster crackers
directions: Mix all ingredients. Garlic powder to taste. Make a day ahead.

title: fruit roll
directions: Mix all together, then fix into a roll; freeze.
Slice when ready to serve.

title: sausage omelet
directions: Heat sausage in heavy 8-inch ovenproof skillet according to package directions.
Remove sausage and keep warm.
Saute the onion and green pepper in sausage skillet over medium-high until tender.
Combine eggs and milk in bowl.
Add the onion, green pepper and tomato.
Melt the butter in the skillet over low heat. Add the egg and vegetable mixture and cook until eggs are almost set.
Arrange the sausage on top of eggs.
Place under the broiler and broil until center is firm and top is lightly browned.
Cut into wedges and serve immediately.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix all but Fritos in large bowl.
Chill, then make Meat Sauce:

title: ritz cracker pie
directions: Mix together the Ritz crackers, chopped nuts and 1/2 cup sugar.
Beat the egg whites, vanilla and 1/2 cup sugar.
Fold cracker mixture into egg whites.
Put in heavily greased pie plate.
Bake for 30 minutes at 300°.
Top with whipped cream or Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with grated chocolate.

title: butterscotch surprise(candy)
directions: Melt butterscotch chips and peanut butter in the top of a double boiler. Stir in nuts and shoestring potatoes. Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper.
Cool for several hours in the refrigerator.
Yields 2 or 3 dozen.

title: steaming oyster stew
directions: Heat milk and cream together until film shimmers over surface. Do not boil.
In separate pan, precook oysters and drain.
Add oysters (slice if you prefer) and butter to hot milk and cream mixture.
Heat but do not boil for 5 minutes more.
Add seasonings and serve at once.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: mazzetti
directions: Cook
beef,
onion
and
garlic.
Add
soups and water; cook. Add 1 package wide noodles, uncooked.
When noodles are done, place
slices
of
cheese, cover and let stand until ready to eat.
This is all cooked in one pot.

title: grandmother fowler's rolls
directions: Place warm water in a mixing bowl. Stir in yeast until dissolved. Add shortening, salt, sugar, egg and 1/2 of flour. Mix well with electric mixer. Mix in remainder of flour well with a spoon or dough hooks.
Turn out into a well greased large mixing bowl. Grease top of dough (I spray it with Pam). Cover and let rise in a warm place until double.

title: summer ginger ale salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add lemonade concentrate and stir to dissolve.
Add ginger ale.
Chill until thick, but not set.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Pour into 2 1/2-quart mold. Chill until firm.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: roast and potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Place roast in medium roaster pan and cover with water.
Add chopped onion, celery, salt and pepper. Cover and let cook 30 minutes. Turn oven down to 325°.
Let cook slowly, approximately 4 hours. Check roast to be sure it is covered with water. After 4 to 4 1/2 hours, add potatoes and carrots.
Cook about 1 1/2 hours or until potatoes are tender.

title: orange julius
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender with 1/2 cup water and enough ice cubes to fill container.
Process until liquified.

title: fruit whip
directions: Prepare Jell-O as directed.
Cut Jell-O into cubes and mix ingredients together.
Cool.

title: baked squash from "black-eyed pea restaurant"
directions: Cut off tips of squash and cut in pieces.
Boil until tender. Drain and mash.
Add eggs, bread crumbs and butter.
Then add sugar, salt, onion and pepper.
Bake in greased casserole at 350° until top is lightly browned, about 45 minutes.
Makes 10 servings.

title: shortbread salad
directions: Mix pudding and buttermilk.
Add oranges (I drain 1 can), Cool Whip (I use 16 ounces) and shortbread cookies.
Refrigerate.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Boil first three ingredients 3 minutes.
Then add peanut butter and oats.
Drop on wax paper.

title: rolled oats cake
directions: Cook oats in water.
Add butter.
Let cool.
Add sugars, coconut and eggs.
Mix in dry ingredients.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 35 to 45
minutes, until light brown.

title: pepper steak
directions: Trim fat from meat and bones.
Cut meat into 4-6 serving pieces.
Grease large skillet, season meat on both sides with salt, brown meat thoroughly.
Set meat to the side;
add onion; cook and stir until tender.
Stir in broth, soy sauce and garlic. Cover; simmer for 10 minutes or until meat is tender.
Add green peppers.
Cover; simmer for 5 minutes.

title: rolled up nut cookies
directions: Dissolve yeast in milk.
Mix all ingredients together and roll up to 90 balls.
Cover and set it in the refrigerator overnight until next day.
The next day, roll the balls on powdered sugar, but don't roll too thin.
Put the filling in the center of the cookie; fold one side of the cookie and then overlap the other side on top.
Slightly greased a cookie sheet using two cookie pans. Place 6 or 7 cookies across and 6 rolls down.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Use apricot or nut filling.

title: crock-pot dessert
directions: Spray crockery with nonstick spray.
Stir in peaches and pour into crock-pot.
Cook on low for four to six hours.

title: dieter's ambrosia
directions: Sprinkle gelatine over ginger ale.
Heat until dissolved.
Do not boil.
Cool.
Mix in other ingredients.
Serves 10 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: veal marsala
directions: Season veal with salt and pepper, then dip in flour, vigorously shaking off the excess.
In a heavy skillet, melt 2 tablespoons margarine with olive oil over moderate heat.
When the foam subsides, add the veal, 3 or 4 at a time, and brown for about 3 minutes on each side.
When done, transfer them to plate.
Pour most of the fat out of the skillet, leaving only a thin film at the bottom.
Add the Marsala and 1/4 cup of broth and boil briskly over high heat for 1 to 2 minutes.
Scrape in any brown fragments clinging to pan.
Return veal to pan; cover and simmer over low heat for 10 to 15 minutes, basting with pan juices until tender. Transfer veal to a heated platter.
Add 1/4 cup broth to sauce in pan and boil briskly, scraping in brown bits.
When sauce has reduced and is syrupy, taste it for seasoning and season as necessary.
Remove the pan from the heat; stir in 2 tablespoons of softened margarine and pour the sauce over the veal.

title: chicken divon
directions: Cook broccoli and place in 9x13 baking dish.
Debone chicken; place on top of broccoli.
Mix mayonnaise, soup, lemon juice and spread on top of chicken.
Brown bread crumbs.
Sprinkle on top with cheese.
Bake 350 degrees 30 minutes.

title: soy-flavored chicken
directions: Skin chicken breasts (optional for low-fat).
Place into a baking dish the breasts.
Add 1/3 cup water and place into a preheated oven at 325°.
After 30 minutes, add soy sauce.
Continue to cook for another 30 minutes, then add chopped pepper and sliced mushrooms.
Continue to cook an additional 20 to 30 minutes.
Turn breasts several times to allow the soy sauce to penetrate the meat. Brown lightly.
Serve with wild, brown or white rice.
A low-fat dish and low-salt.

title: spicy spanish rice
directions: Brown beef.
Add onion, green pepper, salt, brown sugar, chili powder, bay leaf and rest of the ingredients.
Cook, covered, until rice and vegetables are done.
Stir often.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: jodi's broccoli
directions: Cook broccoli according to box directions.
Drain.
Place broccoli in a casserole dish.
Add the butter and Velveeta cheese. Crush crackers and spread over top.
Dot extra butter on top of crackers.
Place in a 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes or until brown on top.

title: orange pecans
directions: Combine sugar and milk in saucepan.
Add vinegar.
Boil until it forms a soft ball in cold water.
Pour mixture over pecan halves.
Add grated rind of 2 oranges and stir until pecans are coated.
Spread on foil to dry.

title: chicken baked in soy sauce
directions: Mix the onions, soy sauce and water and put into roasting pan. Put fryer in roaster, skin side down.
Cook 40 minutes and turn; cook 40 minutes.
Serve with Uncle Ben's seasoned long grain and wild rice.
Serves 15.

title: quick kolacky
directions: Cream the margarine.
Add cream cheese and beat until fluffy. Add flour.
Chill 15 minutes.
Roll out and cut into 2-inch rounds. Make depressions in center of rounds.
Place 1 teaspoon of filling in the center.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: hillbilly slaw
directions: Shred cabbage.
Cut carrot, cucumber, bell pepper and radishes in rings.
Mix sugar, vinegar and oil and pour over vegetables. Toss and refrigerate several hours before serving.
Salt to taste before serving.

title: cream cheese muffins
directions: Combine all ingredients except honey in a large bowl.
Beat at low speed of electric mixer.
Fill baking cup lined muffin tins 1/2 full.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Drizzle with honey. Yields 18 muffins.

title: sweet and sour green beans
directions: Cut bacon into pieces and fry with onion.
Drain off fat.
Add vinegar, sugar, beans and salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: chicken and vegetables pot pie
directions: Combine chicken, mixed vegetables and soups in bowl; mix well. Spoon into greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Spread topping evenly over chicken mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until brown.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: lasagna
directions: In skillet, saute onion.
Add meat and cook until done. Mash garlic
with
salt.
Add
to
meat	with pepper, oregano, parsley, tomatoes,	tomato	sauce
and 1 tablespoon Parmesan. Simmer, covered, 30 minutes.

title: caesar's salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients in a jar and shake well.
Store in refrigerator.

title: easy as 1-2-3 microwave brownies
directions: In a medium bowl, beat together butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla with an electric mixer on medium speed until light and fluffy, 1 to 2 minutes.
Beat in cocoa.
Add flour and beat until well blended.
By hand, stir in pecans.
Spread evenly in a wax paper-lined 8-inch square glass dish.
Cook in a microwave oven on High for 3 minutes. Turn dish a quarter turn and cook 2 1/2 to 3 minutes longer.
Let cool.
Sift powdered sugar over top.
Cut into 16 or 25 squares.

title: oatmeal-raisin muffins
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Cut in shortening until mixture is like coarse crumbs.
Stir in rolled oats.
Combine egg, milk and brown sugar; beat well.
Stir into dry ingredients; add raisins.
Spoon into paper baking cups in muffin pans.
Combine granulated sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle over batter.
Bake in a 425° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: apple crisp
directions: Combined crushed frosted mini-wheats with flour, cinnamon, nutmeg and brown sugar.
Mix well.
Add margarine mixing until crumbly.
Set aside for topping.
Place apples in ungreased 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle topping evenly over apples.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes or until apples are tender and topping is browned.
Serve warm with ice cream.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain juice from pineapple and fruit cocktail.
Reserve to use with pudding.
Combine juice and pudding in small saucepan; bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Mixture should thicken and become clear.
Cool to room temperature.
In large bowl, gently combine the pineapple chunks, oranges and fruit cocktail.
Pour pudding mixture over fruit and toss to coat fruit.
Refrigerate for 2 to 3 hours.
When ready to serve, add bananas and gently combine. Serve immediately.
Bananas may darken after a while.

title: pineapple rice salad
directions: Cooked cup of rice is added to all other ingredients.
Mix well.
Serve.

title: basil tortellini soup
directions: In a large saucepan, bring broth to a boil. Add tortellini; cook until tender, about 6 minutes. Stir in the beans, tomato and basil. Reduce heat; simmer, uncovered, for 5 minutes. Add the vinegar, salt and pepper. Serve with cheese.

title: patsy's pecan pie
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add baking powder and sugar to egg whites.
Add nuts and crackers.
Mix together.
Pour into greased pie pan.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Set and let cool, then put Cool Whip or whipped cream on top.

title: company chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Layer 13 x 9-inch baking pan with dried beef.
Place chicken breasts on top.
Cut bacon in smaller pieces, putting a small strip on each breast.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes.
Mix soup and sour cream.
Remove pan from oven and cover chicken well with soup mixture.
Cover chicken and return to oven for 30 minutes more.
(By covering chicken with tinfoil, your gravy will not cook away.)
Remove and serve with rice or noodles.

title: molasses crinkles
directions: Mix shortening, sugar, egg and molasses very well.
Either stir or sift flour before measuring.
Blend all dry ingredients and stir into wet mixture and chill.
Heat oven to 375°.
Roll dough into 1 1/4-inch ball.
Dip tops in granulated sugar.
Place balls, sugar side up, 3-inches apart on greased baking sheet.
Sprinkle each with 2 to 3 drops water.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or just until set, but not hard.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: krum-kaka
directions: Melt butter and cool.
Beat eggs; add sugar and mix.
Whip the cream.
Add melted butter to eggs and sugar; add whipped cream. Add vanilla and flour.
Use 1 scant teaspoon for each one on Krum-KaKa iron.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on package in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Cool completely.
Break cake into pieces.
Prepare pudding mix as directed on package.
In clear glass punch bowl, layer 1/2 of cake, 1/2 of pudding, 1/2 of cherry pie filling, 1/2 of pineapple and 1/2 of Cool Whip.
Repeat layers, ending with Cool Whip. Garnish with maraschino cherries and nuts.
Cover; refrigerate several hours before serving.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together and pour into a buttered 2-quart dish.
Crush Ritz crackers over top and dot generously with butter.
Bake at 400° for 35 minutes.
Cover if crackers tend to burn.

title: heart-smart wacky cake
directions: In ungreased 8-inch cake pan, mix together flour, sugar, soda and cocoa.
Make 3 wells in flour mixture.
Put vinegar in one, vanilla in one and corn oil in 3rd.
Pour water over all and mix with fork until entirely moist.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes until just done.
Ice as desired.

title: rhubarb nut loaf
directions: Stir together in order given.
Pour into 2 loaf pans, well-greased.

title: blueberry banana pie
directions: Bake pie crust and let cool.
It is not necessary to bake graham cracker crust.
Cover bottom of pie shell with banana slices.
Whip cream cheese and combine with Cool Whip.
Spoon over bananas in pie crust.
Top with blueberries.
Chill 2 to 3 hours before serving.

title: three layer coconut cake
directions: Cream margarine and Crisco until fluffy.
Add sugar gradually. Cream for 10 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour and milk alternately.
Add vanilla; beat for 1 minute after last addition.
Bake at 325° until brown.
Cool; frost with White Cake Icing.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown ground beef with onion; drain. Grease 8 x 13-inch baking dish. Place crushed Doritos in bottom. Pour ground beef and onion mixture over Doritos. Mix together the sauce and soup. Pour over mixture. Cover top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until cheese is melted bubbly.

title: tamale pie
directions: Cook meat, diced onions and garlic.
Mix all well in a casserole.
Grate cheese over top and bake 55 minutes at 350°.

title: butterscotch cheesecake bars
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Preheat oven to 350° (325° for glass dish).
In medium saucepan, melt morsels and margarine.
Stir in crumbs and nuts.
Press 1/2 the mixture firmly into bottom of greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
In large bowl, beat cheese until fluffy, then beat in sweetened condensed milk, vanilla and egg; mix well.
Pour into prepared pan.
Top with remaining crumb mixture. Bake for 25 to 30 minutes, or until toothpick inserted near center comes out clean.
Cool to room temperature.
Chill before cutting into bars.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: frosted cinnamon rolls
directions: Combine 2 cups baking mix and milk in a bowl.
Mix well.
Beat vigorously for 30 seconds, adding enough remaining baking mix to make moderate dough. Knead 10 times on floured surface. Roll into 1/2-inch thick rectangle.
Spread with butter.
Mix sugar and cinnamon. Sprinkle over butter.

Top with raisins and nuts. Roll as for jelly roll to enclose filling; cut into 1-inch slices. Place on baking sheet. Bake at 450° for 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown. Blend confectioners sugar with a small amount of water.
Drizzle over rolls. Cool for 5 minutes.
Yields 1 dozen.

title: chicken and pasta neapolitan
directions: In a large skillet over medium heat, heat oil.
Add chicken, onion and garlic.
Cook 5 minutes, stirring frequently or until chicken is no longer pink.
Stir in tomato sauce, wine, sugar and seasonings.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat.
Cook, covered, stirring occasionally for 20 minutes or until thickened.

title: banana bread(low-fat)
directions: Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: chicken green bean casserole
directions: Melt butter.
Add water and dressing.
Put 1/2 dressing in casserole (8 1/2 x 10 x 1 1/2-inch).
Cook and drain beans.
Layer on top of dressing.
Add a layer of almonds, followed with split up chicken breast pieces.
Cover with remaining dressing, then combine the soup and chicken broth; blend until smooth.
Pour soup mixture over entire casserole.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes at 325°.

title: penne all'arrabbiata(milano, italy)
directions: Heat the oil and gently fry the chopped onion and garlic until softened.
Add the chili pepper and fry gently for 1 minute.
Add the tomatoes with their juice, sugar, salt and pepper to taste and cook on a high flame, uncovered, for about 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
When the sauce is reduced and thick, check the season.
If you like a smoother sauce, you can pass the sauce through the medium disk of a food mill.
I usually just chop up the tomatoes with a fork and leave the sauce a bit chunky.
Add the chopped parsley just before serving.
Cook the pasta following the directions on the packet very carefully to avoid overcooking.

title: pam's barbecue ribs
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together and roll ribs in this mixture until well coated.
Place ribs in greased roaster pan with lid. Blend together tomato soup, vinegar and onion.
Pour this over ribs.
Bake in oven very slowly at 250° to 300° for 3 or 3 1/2 hours.

title: fantasy fudge
directions: Stir together sugar, margarine and milk.
Bring to a full boil, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Gradually stir in chocolate chips until melted.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased pans; cool at room temperature.
Cut into squares.

title: rolled cheese appetizers
directions: Mix filling together.
Spread onto tortillas.
Let refrigerate about 1 hour.
Slice into pinwheels and serve.
Great to make ahead and serve.

title: diet natural food
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 300° until lightly browned, stirring often.

title: dried beef spread
directions: Mix and chill for at least an hour before serving with crackers.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream the butter and sugar together.
Beat eggs. Add the bananas.
Sift the flour.
Add the salt and sift together again, then add alternately with the banana mixture. Add the nuts.
Add last the soda with a little warm water.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes in an angel food pan.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and enjoy.

title: mexican sausage
directions: Mix ingredients by hand.
Let mixture set overnight in refrigerator.
Make into patties and cook on slightly greased grill or frying pan.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Cook corn bread to package directions. Cool. It's better if kept for 24 hours, then crumbled. Add all vegetables. Cool in refrigerator about 1 hour. Stir in Miracle Whip. Add cheese.

title: oatmeal apple raisin muffins
directions: Beat egg; stir in remaining ingredients, mixing just to moisten.
Pour into 12 greased muffin cups until 3/4 full.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve cool or hot with butter.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Warm tomato soup; add gelatine to soften.
Add other ingredients.
Allow to set up in refrigerator.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Place Velveeta and 1 cup milk in thick boiler and melt.
Add the Kraft package cheese powder.
Beat egg and pour into cheese mixture and stir.
Place boiled macaroni in Corning dish.
Add cheese mixture over this.
Cook in 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook bacon, crumble and set aside.
In bacon fat, cook onion, pepper and mushrooms until tender.
Stir in flour, chicken broth, cream and pimento.
Simmer until sauce thickens.
Add salt, pepper, bacon, chicken or turkey and cooked spaghetti.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: banana split cake
directions: Drain pineapple.
Slice bananas and dip in lemon juice.
Mix melted butter and graham cracker crumbs and press into 13X9 pan. In mixer, mix powdered sugar, butter and eggs for 15 minutes. Spread over crumbs.
Cover with crushed pineapple.
Cover pineapple with banana slices.
Top with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with nuts and cherries.
Chill overnight.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Combine sugar, vinegar, mustard seed, celery seed and turmeric.
Place in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Mix onions and salt with cucumbers.
Put these in jars and pour cooked spices over cucumbers.
Follow directions on lids of canning jars to seal.

title: health cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a bowl, sift together the flour, salt and baking soda.
In a second bowl, place all the other ingredients.
Add the flour mixture to bowl 2 and beat until well mixed.
Batter will be lumpy.
Place in tube pan and bake for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Do not open oven.
When cooled, remove from pan and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: chocolate chip zucchini bread
directions: Cream sugar, oil and baking chocolate; add eggs and mix.
Add remaining ingredients and mix.
Spray 3 small loaf pans with Pam; pour batter in and fill halfway.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown steak with green pepper and onion and cut into small bite-size pieces.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over egg noodles or rice.

title: turtle brownies
directions: Prepare cake mix according to box instructions.
Generously grease a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Pour 1/2 of cake batter into the pan.
Bake for 10 minutes at temperature recommended on box instructions.
While cake is baking, melt caramels in saucepan with the can of milk.
Remove cake from oven; pour caramel mixture over hot cake.
Sprinkle chocolate chips on top of caramel.
Pour remaining batter evenly over the top.
Bake for 25 minutes, or until top layer is done.
Let cool completely; cut into squares. Makes between 30 to 36 squares.

title: macaroni lunch
directions: Pan fry sausage into crumbled pieces and drain on paper towels.
In a large boiler, bring to boil tomatoes, tomato sauce, water (add more or less water according to your liking), salt and pepper, oil and celery seed.
Add sausage and macaroni.
Stir well, turn off, place on lid and leave covered 5 minutes.
Serve with crackers and salad or coleslaw.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Mix and put half of mixture in 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Mix brown sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle 1/2 brown sugar mixture on batter and swirl in.
Pour rest of batter in and use rest of brown sugar mixture.
Bake at 325° for about 40 minutes.
